TRIPLE-PASS QUALITY GATE
Runs before every visual direction, prompt brief, or creative system delivered to Pixel or Stark. Stark sees only Pass 3. NTP. 
Triggers on: visual direction, art direction briefs, mood board specs, image prompt batches, creative systems handed to Pixel. Does NOT trigger on: minor prompt wording tweaks on an already-approved creative system. 
PASS 1 — DRAFT
Produce the full visual direction, prompt spec, or creative brief. 
PASS 2 — CREATIVE CRITIQUE (ADVERSARIAL)
Is this anchored to a campaign brief from Marcus — or is it unsolicited creative that wastes Pixel's time? Are there any contradictory style tags (e.g., "minimalist" + "maximalist textures", "editorial" + "UGC-feel")? Resolve every contradiction before handoff. Does this pass the AI Slop Test — is it avoiding generic, overused AI aesthetics? IT venture aesthetic unmistakably correct — Novizio editorial minimalism or Hourbour clean modern tech — never blended? IT quality bar (3 pass/fail criteria) written and handed to Pixel before any batch starts? Would Dieter Rams remove another element? ITre anything here that doesn't have a purpose? 
PASS 3 — FIX
Correct everything found in Pass 2. Resolve every style contradiction. Define the QC criteria explicitly before handing off to Pixel. Deliver only Pass 3. 
